**Summary of the upload mechanism:** It uses `XMLHttpRequest` (not `fetch`) to POST a `multipart/form-data` body to `POST /api/upload`. The file field is named `"file"`. On a 2xx response it parses the JSON and reads `data.url`, then stores that URL into `form.image_url` via `setField`.The frontend code looks correct. The issue must be on the backend. Let me check and fix the backend upload endpoint directly.

